// =====================================================================
// 01-create-database.kql
// Run against an existing Eventhouse cluster, NOT against an empty cluster.
// The PowerShell module's Initialize-FDAObservability invokes this for you;
// you only run it manually if you are bootstrapping a database outside the
// module.
// =====================================================================

// Database creation is performed via Fabric REST (Eventhouse item create) and
// then via Kusto Management Endpoint:
//   .create database FDAObs persist (
//       @"https://<adls>.dfs.core.windows.net/<container>/md",
//       @"https://<adls>.dfs.core.windows.net/<container>/data"
//   )
// Inside a Fabric Eventhouse, the database is created as a Fabric item; the
// module calls POST /v1/workspaces/{workspaceId}/eventhouses/{eventhouseId}/databases.

// After the database exists, the rest of the scripts (02..08) are executed
// against it.

.show database FDAObs principals
